The paper deals with image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of semantic segmentation networks for feature extraction suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The robustness and accuracy of the proposed method suggest that it may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the method to aerial images suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of the method for registration suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO).
